Condition : 6 - No development (except demolition, archaeological investigations, ground condition investigations and intrusive site surveys and other enabling works: site clearance; soil storage; remedial works in respect of any contamination or any other adverse ground conditions; erection of any temporary means of enclosure and land raising and any piling or foundations) shall take place until details and samples of all facing materials are submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The samples and details shall include:
- brick (including brick and mortar on-site sample panel min. 2m x 2m);
- cladding materials (including system specifications/details and on-site samples) (where relevant);
- window treatment (including sections/reveals and on-site sample);
- all privacy measures, (including obscure glazing details, privacy screens etc.); and
- balustrading treatment (including details/sections/materials);
- any other materials/details to be used (noting in particular the final external treatment adjacent to the front entrances).
The development shall then be carried out in accordance with the approved details and maintained as such thereafter.

Condition : 19 - Prior to the commencement of the development (except demolition, archaeological investigations, ground condition investigations and intrusive site surveys and other enabling works: site clearance; soil storage; remedial works in respect of any contamination or any other adverse ground conditions; erection of any temporary means of enclosure and land raising and any piling or foundations), details of both hard and soft landscape works shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The works shall then be carried out as approved.
The detailed landscaping scheme shall include:
- soft planting: including any grass and turf areas, trees, planters, shrub and herbaceous areas including details of species, sizes, numbers/densities and sections of landscaped areas;
- a 'Tree Planting Statement' providing full details, locations, specifications and construction methods for all purpose-built tree pits and associated above ground features, including specifications for tree protection and a stated volume of suitable growing medium to facilitate and promote the healthy development of the proposed trees, ensuring each tree has a soil volume equivalent of 0.6 times its canopy area at maturity;
- hard landscaping: including ground surfaces, kerbs, edges, ridge and flexible paving, furniture, steps, refuse disposal points and if applicable synthetic surfaces for both ground level and roof terrace level (where relevant) demonstrating how 'Home Zone Environmental' principles have been applied;
- fences and walls and any other boundary treatments;
- any play spaces and play equipment;
- any signage (Legible London) and information boards;
- brown (biodiversity) roofs/green walls (where relevant);
- any CCTV equipment;
- an external lighting strategy; and
- any other landscaping feature(s) forming part of the scheme (e.g. visitor cycle stands, etc.).
The submission shall include a management programme for the lifetime of the development, which

Condition : 24 - No unit shall be occupied until a Car Park Management Plan has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The Plan shall include the following:
"	Details and location of 20% electric vehicle charging points (min. 7kW/h) and details of a further 20% passive provision;
"	A strategy detailing how the uptake in electric vehicle charging points is monitored to bring into use passive charging points when required;
"	Details of how parking outside of designated bays will be managed. 
The car parking areas shall thereafter be managed in compliance with the approved Car Park Management Plan.
